{"abstract":[{"text":"With iOS 5, you can customize the look of your app controls using the new Appearance APIs. The new Appearance Proxy API allows you to efficiently apply a custom appearance to your views and controls, including built-in controls such navigation, tab, and toolbars. These customizations can be applied across your entire app or independently on a per-control basis.","type":"text"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Read Transcript","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2011\/114\/"}},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11"]]},"metadata":{"title":"Customizing the Appearance of UIKit Controls","role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC11","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc11-114-customizing-the-appearance-of-uikit-controls"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11-114-Customizing-the-Appearance-of-UIKit-Controls","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"article","references":{"WWDC11.jpeg":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC11.jpeg","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","id